---
title: "init-project — Scaffold + Detect Stack + Detect Monorepo + Discover Modules + Detect Layers"
---
%%{init: {'theme': 'neutral'}}%%
sequenceDiagram
    actor User
    participant Claude
    participant FS as File System
    participant Glob as Glob Tool

    note over Claude: Capture start timestamp
    Claude->>Claude: START_TS = date +%s<br/>RUN_TS = date -u +%Y%m%dT%H%M%SZ<br/>DISPLAY_TS = date +%Y%m%d-%H%M%S

    note over Claude,FS: Scaffold .claude structure
    Claude->>FS: Check if .claude/ exists
    FS-->>Claude: Exists / not found

    alt .claude/ already exists
        Claude->>User: .claude/ already exists.<br/>[1] Merge — keep existing, fill gaps (recommended)<br/>[2] Overwrite — start fresh, delete existing content<br/>[3] Abort
        User-->>Claude: Choice
        break User chose abort
            Claude->>User: Aborted
        end
    end

    Claude->>FS: Create .claude/ structure<br/>(rules/, docs/, skills/, sequences/,<br/>agents/, output-styles/)<br/>+ .gitkeep in empty dirs
    FS-->>Claude: Directories created
    Claude->>FS: Create CLAUDE.md, CLAUDE.local.md,<br/>settings.json, settings.local.json
    FS-->>Claude: OK
    Claude->>FS: Append .gitignore entries
    FS-->>Claude: OK

    note over Claude,Glob: Detect stack
    Claude->>Glob: Pass 1: build markers<br/>(*.sln, go.mod, Cargo.toml, package.json)
    Glob-->>Claude: Primary stack
    Claude->>Glob: Pass 2: file type census<br/>(count extensions, exclude node_modules/.git/build)
    Glob-->>Claude: File counts per extension
    Claude->>Claude: Map extensions → stacks<br/>Flag secondary stacks (50+ files)
    Claude->>Glob: Pass 2b: frontend detection<br/>(package.json + framework config,<br/>apps/*/, web/, client/, ui/, projects/*/)
    Glob-->>Claude: Candidate frontend roots
    Claude->>FS: Pass 3: tooling + conventions<br/>(formatter, linter, CI, git)
    FS-->>Claude: Tooling profile

    Claude->>User: Detected stack:<br/>  Primary:   <language> <framework><br/>  Secondary: <lang> (<N> files)<br/>  Frontend:  <roots><br/>  Tooling:   <formatter> <linter> <CI><br/>[1] Correct — proceed<br/>[2] Override primary stack<br/>[3] Add/remove secondary stack
    User-->>Claude: choice

    note over Claude,Glob: Detect monorepo
    Claude->>Glob: Check pnpm-workspace.yaml, nx.json,<br/>go.work, Cargo.toml[workspace],<br/>multiple package.json
    Glob-->>Claude: Monorepo signals

    Claude->>User: Project type:<br/>[1] Single-stack — one language, one build<br/>[2] Monorepo — multiple packages/apps<br/>[3] Feature monorepo — one language, multiple feature modules<br/>(detected: <suggested type>)
    User-->>Claude: choice

    note over Claude,Glob: Discover modules
    alt Single-stack
        Claude->>Glob: Scan projects/*, src/*, packages/*, apps/*
        Glob-->>Claude: Module list
    else Monorepo
        loop For each area
            Claude->>Glob: Scan area packages
            Glob-->>Claude: Modules in area
        end
    end

    Claude->>User: Found N modules:<br/>  module-a  (85 files)<br/>  module-b  (30 files)<br/>  ...<br/>[1] Confirm all<br/>[2] Remove specific modules (type numbers)<br/>[3] Add missed path
    User-->>Claude: choice

    note over Claude,Glob: Detect logical layers
    Claude->>Glob: Group modules by shared patterns + imports
    Glob-->>Claude: Module clusters
    Claude->>Claude: Map clusters to logical layers

    Claude->>User: Found N logical layers:<br/>  Frontend  (3 modules)<br/>  Features  (20 modules)<br/>  Common    (2 modules)<br/>[1] Confirm layers<br/>[2] Adjust grouping<br/>[3] Skip layer detection
    User-->>Claude: choice
